The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 May is 42,042 (4,866.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 May, there were 106 new confirmed cases (12.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 April, there were 140 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (34 fewer cases).
